The paper proposes a novel proximal-gradient algorithm for minimizing TV regularized least-squares cost functional, which is a common problem in image processing and computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the convergence of the proposed method, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of TV for solving large scale imaging inverse problems, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for solving a common optimization problem, which could also make it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
